      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Once the meat-free chick'n is crispy, transfer it to a plate and set aside for later, then return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> and <strong>onion</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> ginger</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
